  if (typeof a === 'number' && typeof b === 'number') {
    return a + b; // Adding numbers
  }
  if (typeof a ==='string' && typeof b ==='string') {
    return a + b; // Concatenating strings
  }
  throw new Error('Parameters must be both numbers or both strings');
}
```

This version of the function can handle both numbers and strings, throwing an error if the types don't match.

